columns_description: Time at which 911 operator first identified call as being fire or emergency medical related.
Unique Sno911 identifier. Each responding agency has it's own incident #, but only one CallID.
Number by which each responding agency identifies a call. The same call can have multiple incident #s if multiple agencies respond.
911 call types categorized as Fire, Medical, or Other. Blank values most commonly represent incorrect dispatches of fire vehicles to police calls and not actual incidents.
911 call type code. Not necessarily what firefighters found when they arrived, but rather how the dispatcher classified it based on the caller's statements.
Description of 911 call type code.
Ranks urgency of call from 1-5, 1 being the most urgent. Emergency situations are 1-3, where fire departments respond with lights and sirens.
Incident location, generalized to the 100 block. Calls with no location are usually highway or freeway responses with no corresponding street address.
Fire department that has authority based on location of call - not necessarily which department responded.
Everett neighborhood of call location. Blank value indicates call was outside city limits.
Fire station traditionally responsible for call location. For high priority calls 911 dispatches the closest available unit, which may or may not be from this station.
Smaller zones that identify which fire department is responsible for location. Everett Fire quadrants start with BA. Does not always agree with city limits.
Latitude/longitude of call, generalized to nearest 100 block.
Fire department whose unit(s) were dispatched to the call. May not match Call Location Fire Department. Incident # corresponds to this department.
Fire or emergency medical vehicle number dispatched to call. E=Engine, L=Ladder, M=Medic, A=Aid Unit.
Order in which this unit arrived on scene of this call. Blank value indicates unit did not arrive.
For easier sorting of calls by year.

For rolling up unit dispatch information to the CallID level. Filter by CALLROW to return 1 row per call no matter how many agencies dispatched.
For rolling up unit dispatch information to the Incident level. Filter by INCIDENTROW to return 1 row per agency dispatched, no matter how many units.
